@startuml
title Vault Management Metadata - State Machine Diagram (Current)
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #f7e9dc
  BorderColor #d9c2a8
}

[*] --> Unknown

state Unknown
state Rotating
state Ok
state Failed

Unknown --> Ok : init_keyring success\nset_last_rotation_result("ok", reason)
Unknown --> Failed : init_keyring failed\nset_last_rotation_result("failed", reason)

Ok --> Rotating : rotate_and_rewrap start\nset_last_rotation_result("rotating", "rotate_in_progress")
Ok --> Rotating : rewrap_all_dek start\nset_last_rotation_result("rotating", "rewrap_in_progress")
Ok --> Rotating : finalize_inflight_bridge start\nset_last_rotation_result("rotating", "bridge_finalize_in_progress")

Rotating --> Ok : success\nset_last_rotation_result("ok", reason)\nset_last_rotated_at(optional)
Rotating --> Failed : failure\nset_last_rotation_result("failed", reason)

Failed --> Rotating : retry lifecycle operation
Failed --> Ok : successful retry

Ok --> Ok : run_if_due (due=false)\nmetadata result unchanged

note right of Rotating
  run_id is updated on each lifecycle attempt
  via set_last_rotation_run_id(run_id)
end note

note bottom
  State values reflect repository metadata:
  last_rotation_result = rotating | ok | failed
end note

@enduml
